<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-194-309 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 542 949</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  March 26 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for PCs: animation package for low-end computers. (P11Enterprises' P11 software) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rohrbough, Linda Houser.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   P11 Enterprises (Product introduction).andO;Product:   P11 (Educational software) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionAnimationGraphics Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR PCS: Animation Package For Low-end Computers 03/26/91 LOS ANGELES,CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1991 MAR 26 (NB) -- P11 is a license-free, runtimesoftware designed for novices who wish to create animations on low-end IBMcompatible computers.andP;  Aimed at the educational, art and advertising markets,the package is designed for the quick production of computer animatedgraphics.andM;As supplied, P11 comes with sample animations, a beginner's tutorial,icon-based drawing tools, and on-line help.andP;  It allows users to animate over8,000 frames at once with timings which are claimed to be accurate to within1/1000 of a second.andP;  The package, which also features a powerful commandlanguage, and a list of resource materials to help users learn animationtechniques, also imports files from within other programs.andM;Intended to run on the IBM PC, XT, and AT or compatible computers in aminimum of CGA graphics mode, the company claims the resultant animation issmooth even on a slow PC.andP;  P11 animations can be created to take advantage ofcomputers with higher capability and is designed to take advantage of EMM ifavailable.andM;The package retails for $129.95 and is available from P11 Enterprises, P.O.andO;Box 5185, Bridgeport, CT 06610, 203-366-0258.andM;(Linda Houser Rohrbough/19910326/Press Contact: P11 Enterprises, RussellHoffman, 213-934-2064)</TEXT></DOC>